Info about issue-related messages and conversations (message content isnâ€™t included)

You can select which messages and conversations, if any, to include in your feedback. Only info about your messages and conversations is sent to Google, not the text or attachments in those messages.

Info about your messages and conversations includes the phone numbers and email addresses of senders and receivers, the message type (SMS, MMS or RCS), the message size and any subject line, the sent and received dates, local message and conversation IDs, the local message status and the internal message path (URL). Your text and attachments are not sent to Google.

This info helps validate assumptions and identify factors contributing to the issue, for faster, more efficient understanding of the issue.
